## PHASE 2: CORE FEATURE — Wire Geo-Matching (Day 3-4)

> **Why second:** The matching algorithm is the *entire point* of the platform. An examiner who sees `locationScore = 50 // Placeholder` will dock major points. This is the single highest-ROI change.

### 2.1 Wire Haversine into Matching Service
**File:** [matching.service.js:126-131](file:///Users/mohamedyaser/Documents/LifeLink/src/services/matching.service.js#L126)
**Problem:** `geo.js` has a working `calculateDistance()` and `getLocationScore()` — but `matching.service.js` imports `geo.js` and **never uses it**. Location score is hardcoded to 50.
**The Fix:**
```javascript
// Replace lines 126-131 in matching.service.js
let locationScore = 50;
if (donor.location?.coordinates?.lat && donor.location?.coordinates?.lng) {
  const hospitalLoc = request.hospitalId?.location;
  if (hospitalLoc?.coordinates?.lat && hospitalLoc?.coordinates?.lng) {
    const distance = geoUtil.calculateDistance(
      { latitude: donor.location.coordinates.lat, longitude: donor.location.coordinates.lng },
      { latitude: hospitalLoc.coordinates.lat, longitude: hospitalLoc.coordinates.lng }
    );
    locationScore = geoUtil.getLocationScore(distance, 100);
  }
}
```
> [!IMPORTANT]
> The `geo.js` utility uses `latitude/longitude` property names while the User model stores `lat/lng`. The adapter code above bridges this gap.

**Also fix `findCompatibleRequests`** (line ~163) — it calls `.populate('hospitalId', 'address location')` but never uses the location for scoring. Apply the same geo-scoring logic there.

**Effort:** 2-3 hours. **Impact:** Transforms the core feature from placeholder to functional. **Examiner impact:** Massive.

### 2.2 Add Pagination to Matching (DB-Level)
**File:** [matching.service.js:99](file:///Users/mohamedyaser/Documents/LifeLink/src/services/matching.service.js#L99)
**Problem:** `Donor.find({ isAvailable: true })` loads ALL donors into memory. N+1 queries for existing donations.
**Action:** 
1. Add blood type filter to the initial query (reduces result set by ~87.5%)
2. Use `$lookup` aggregation to check existing donations instead of N+1
3. Add `.limit()` to cap results

```javascript
const donors = await Donor.find({
  isAvailable: true,
  ...(request.type === 'blood' && request.bloodType 
    ? { bloodType: { $in: getCompatibleDonorTypes(request.bloodType) } }
    : {}),
}).limit(200);
```
**Effort:** 3-4 hours. **Impact:** Prevents OOM at scale, shows performance awareness.

