## PHASE 3: TESTING (Day 5-8)

> **Why third:** Zero tests is the single biggest scoring gap. Even 10 well-chosen tests demonstrate professional practice and jump the testing score from 3/10 to 7/10.

### 3.1 Setup Test Infrastructure
**Action:**
1. `npm install --save-dev vitest` (fast, ESM-native, zero-config)
2. Update `package.json`:
```json
"scripts": {
  "test": "vitest run",
  "test:watch": "vitest"
}
```
3. Create `vitest.config.js` with `globalSetup` for MongoDB memory server
4. `npm install --save-dev mongodb-memory-server` for isolated DB tests

**Effort:** 1-2 hours.

### 3.2 Priority Test Targets (Maximum Impact, Minimum Effort)

| Priority | Test File | What to Test | Why |
|----------|-----------|-------------|-----|
| 1 | `auth.service.test.js` | register, login, 2FA flow, OTP flow, token refresh | Most complex service, highest bug surface |
| 2 | `matching.service.test.js` | Blood type compatibility matrix, eligibility checks, geo-scoring | Core feature — must prove it works |
| 3 | `reward.service.test.js` | Points award, dedup, tier promotion, redemption | Most impressive subsystem — tests prove the atomic guarantees |
| 4 | `middleware.test.js` | Auth middleware token checks, role middleware, maintenance bypass | Security-critical paths |

**Target:** 30-40 tests covering the critical paths. Don't aim for 80% coverage — aim for **100% coverage of the happy paths and critical edge cases**.

**Effort:** 4-5 days. **Impact:** Testing score jumps from 3/10 to 7-8/10.

### 3.3 Fix CI to Run Tests
Once tests exist, the GitHub Actions workflow will automatically pass. Green ✅ on every commit.

