## WHAT NOT TO WORK ON (Time Wasters)

| Item | Why Skip |
|------|----------|
| **Docker/docker-compose** | Nice-to-have but zero scoring impact for a graduation project. The demo runs fine without it. |
| **WebSocket real-time** | Major effort (2+ days), low scoring impact, and the Flutter client likely doesn't support it yet. |
| **File upload system** | Out of scope for current features. Would require new models, storage, and client support. |
| **HIPAA compliance** | Academic project, not a production healthcare system. Mentioning awareness in docs is sufficient. |
| **Redis caching** | Over-engineering. The in-memory cache for maintenance mode is enough. |
| **Payment integration** | The reward system is gamification, not commerce. Adding payments adds complexity with no demo value. |
| **API versioning refactor** | The dual-mount pattern (`/auth` + `/api/v1/auth`) works fine. Refactoring is cosmetic. |
| **Sentry/APM** | Production concern, not graduation concern. |

